course_title: Women's Health Gender Related Nurse Practitioner Clinical Practicum III
course_description: This clinical course integrates health promotion and achievement of patient health care goals in a primary care setting. Students will continue to refine their clinical management and leadership skills focusing on competent care delivery that is inclusive as they transition to the WHGRNP role.
prerequisites: NRSG 613D prerequisite and NRSG 658D co-requisite or equivalent transfer credit. Students must enroll in NRSG 658D first.
